@mik-laj - 

I've updated the documentation based on your feedback.  Please let me know if that is ok and if you have any additional recommendations.

Thanks

@XD-DENG I have seen that issue also a long time ago already. Here the build still continues en getting the raw log is still possible. Travis sometimes even kills jobs when the log is to long, this change at least reduce the chance on that.

@ashb I think that would be awesome. Don't like using unmaintained package of course ;).

Although I think switching to pytest would hit other testing issues, like statefull tests because the order is changed. I have seen a lot of those problems in the past.

Merging this would at least reduce the logs for now. So can this be merged knowing this is a workaround till @ashb successfully makes the switch to pytest?

@fokko -> 
* .tox removed
* .bash_aliases and .inputrc are removed from the Dockerfile
